    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-06-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-06-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="122"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Beaupré</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-06-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Colombian Government apparently does not appreciate the gravity of the
                    situation. The canal negotiations were initiated by Colombia, and were
                    energetically pressed upon this Government for several years. The propositions
                    presented by Colombia, with slight modifications, were finally accepted by us.
                    In virtue of this agreement our Congress reversed its previous judgment and
                    decided upon the Panama route. If Colombia should now reject the treaty or
                    unduly delay its ratification, the friendly understanding between the two
                    countries would be so seriously compromised that action might be taken by the
                    Congress next winter which every friend of Colombia would regret. Confidential.
                    Communicate substance of this verbally to the minister of foreign affairs. If he
                    desires it, give him a copy in form of memorandum.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
